{"lemma":"سُكّان","slug":"سُكّان","root":"س.ك.ن","root_slug":"س-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ساكِن","root":"سكن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20268","n20269"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%91%D8%A7%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inhabitant"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"stationary, motionless, still, unmoving"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unvowelled"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"placid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to live together, to share quarters with (someone)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb سَكَنَ (sakana, “to live, to inhabit”)."},"ipa":["/saː.kin/","/saː.ka.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20268","headword_ar":"سَكَّانٌ","root":"skn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A maker of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakaAkiyn","text_ar":"سَكَاكِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knives"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (ISd, L, K, *) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikiynN","text_ar":"سِكِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISd, L;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakaAkiyniY~N","text_ar":"سَكَاكِينِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, L, K,) which latter is held by ISd to be post-classical, being formed from the pl., whereas by rule it should be formed from the sing. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["ISd","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20269","headword_ar":"سُكَّانٌ","root":"skn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*anab","text_ar":"ذَنَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, MA, Mgh, L,) [i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rudder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, PS,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a ship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, MA, Mgh, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of which it is rightly directed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, * L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steady;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L;) its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadof","text_ar":"خَدْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AA, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayozuraAnN","text_ar":"خَيْزُرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawovalN","text_ar":"كَوْثَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the same, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its tiller"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A 'Obeyd, L:) it is an Arabic word. (L.) Hence the saying of Tarafeh, (L,) likening to it the elevated neck of a she-camel, as being long, and quick in motion, (EM p. 73,) [and thus app. applying it to the upper and narrow part of a rudder,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kasuk~aAni buwSiYK bidijolapa muSoEidi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, EM,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~aAn","text_ar":"سُكَّان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a vessel of the sort called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buwSiY~","text_ar":"بُوصِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascending the Tigris"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (EM.)       -A2-  Also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkinN","text_ar":"سَاكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (L, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","S","MA","Mgh","L","KL","PS","EM"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}